    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.83-84_0001" />
                <note type="curatorial">197 House Collection</note>                
                <fw type="curatorial">83</fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Branson, Dec 31, '31</dateline>
                
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Comrade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I've just wired you.</p>
                
                <p>The news hit us hard, and our feeling for you and Mary is warm and deep. I am not going to juggle hollow words, but I <hi rend="underline">do love you</hi>, best and dearest of comrades; and I <hi rend="underline">care</hi>. You are not going to be downed by this, I know, for you have great reserves of philosophical insight and good sense to draw upon. It is good that you two had a happy trip together last fall and that Mrs. House went while still feeling the glow of Morrie's triumph and with the happy consciousness of Mary's goodness and beauty.</p>
                
                <p>I'm wondering when we are going to be together again. We must plan to this end.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Endless love, Comrade!</salute>
                
                <signed>Jno.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.83-84_0002"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">84</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    Neihardt
                    Branson.
                    Mo.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    <unclear cert="high">BRANSO</unclear>N JAN 1 <unclear/> -AM 1931 MO.
                </ab>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE 2 CENTS 2</p>
                </figure>
                
